            <abstract>
                <p><foreign xml:lang="gez">Qǝne</foreign> with three lines attributed to 
                    <persName ref="PRS14574GabraLeul" cert="high" corresp="SD">Gabra Ləʿul</persName> 
                    in the manuscript. It appears that the first word of the first line was originally (in the Vorlage?)
                    intended as a <foreign xml:lang="gez">qǝne</foreign>-type indication, identifying this as a 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">śəllāse</foreign>-type <foreign xml:lang="gez">qǝne</foreign>.
                    However, according to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Guidi1900Qene"/><citedRange>464</citedRange></bibl>, 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">śəllāse</foreign>-type <foreign xml:lang="gez">qǝne</foreign>s
                    have six lines. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Habtemichael1998Ufficio"/><citedRange>216</citedRange></bibl>, 
                    in contrast, who says they have three lines.</p>
            </abstract>
